  "prompt": "Will Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice flop?",
  "response": "\"Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice\" was released in March 2016 and had a mixed critical reception, with some viewers enjoying the film while others criticized it for its pacing and tone. Upon its release, it did make substantial box office earnings, exceeding $800 million worldwide, but fell short of its expected financial goals, especially when considering the high production and marketing costs.\n\nWhile it did not \"flop\" in terms of box office numbers, the film is often discussed as a disappointment in terms of critical reception and its impact on the DC Extended Universe. Subsequent titles were influenced by its performance and reception. If you're looking for further analysis or discussion regarding its legacy or impact on future DC films, feel free to ask!",
